HEADWORD: Tipstock
<hw>Tip"stock`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The detachable or
movable fore part of a gunstock, lying beneath the barrel or barrels,
and forming a hold for the left hand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tipsy</ent>⟦br⟧
